{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|凡|鳥|t2=bird|ls=psc}}.

In the oracle bone script, the script of {{och-l|鳳}} was often phonetically borrowed to represent {{och-l|風|wind}}. Subsequent forms of the script of {{zh-l|*風}} were also derived from parts of the bronze inscription of {{lang|zh|鳳}}.
